#: ../../tutorials/introductions/intro_quantum.rst:11
msgid ""
"Quantum refers to the fact that in quantum physics, certain properties of"
" particles (like energy, position, and spin) can only take on discrete "
"values, or \"quanta\". This is in contrast to classical physics, where "
"these properties can vary continuously. The quantum nature of particles "
"leads to phenomena that are fundamentally different from classical "
"physics, which in some cases allows for new capabilities that are not "
"possible with classical computers."
